==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fainting
<hw>Faint"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Syncope, or loss of
consciousness owing to a sudden arrest of the blood supply to the brain,
the face becoming pallid, the respiration feeble, and the heat's beat
weak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fainting fit</b></col>, <cd>a fainting or swoon;
syncope.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faintish</ent>⟦br⟧
